abstracts.cdata!:
A loan of US$25.0 million is proposed to
            finance 50 percent of the costs of a population project over
            the next five years. The project is an integrated package
            designed to assist the broad program objectives of the
            population program and to strengthen the health and family
            planning delivery system of the department of health. It
            consists of two main components. The first supports a number
            of activities of the Population Commission
            (Information-Education-Communication, training and
            strengthening the regional offices of the POPCOM), while the
            second supports the department of health, mainly through the
            construction and equipping of 11 training centers and 205
            rural health units through which health and family planning
            services would be delivered to the population.
